FBIS4-38635 "drsov105_a_94036" FBIS-SOV-94-105 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Former Nuclear Test Site To Be Handed Over to Kazakhstan Former Nuclear Test Site To Be Handed Over to Kazakhstan LD0106091494 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0630 GMT 1 Jun 94 LD0106091494 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] Russia is ready to hand over the nuclear test range near Kurchatov to Kazakhstan as of 1 June. The Kurchatov test range was used for nuclear tests from 1949 until 1991, when the moratorium on nuclear arms tests was introduced. Kazakhstan proposes to turn Kurchatov into an international center for radiological, engineering, and medical research.
